rComments: Dr. El Nachef delivered the course in a very comprehensible manner and was helpful. There are a lot of mechanisms to learn so start early! Practicing using her problem sets and textbook was helpful for me.

the sweetest prof ever... she curved all the marks (for the two midterms and the final ALTHOUGH everything was covered in class). She explains the concepts very clearly (at the end of the course, I could figure out the mechanisms without even memorizing them). She wants us to understand all the details and answers every question. I love her!
Orgo 2 with Claudia was a good experience. However, the course was rushed towards the end. Be prepared to study hard.
Nice, but goes through way too much content too fast

HOLAY. She has amazing lectures, very passionate, and you can understand them, so you end up feeling confident. her practice questions though, come out from no where, but thankfully she shows you how to answer them. MIDTERMS/EXAMS; brutaallll. you think you know what you're doing, but it's all a trick :( abort mission yall.

I took her class in the summer because people recommended her but I was very disappointed. Midterm 1 was insanely hard and nothing like the past midterms she posted. She was reluctant to share past exams because she makes them different every year. After both her French and English courses got a 51% avg she pointed the finger/blamed the students.

Midterm is difficult.
She speaks very fast in class and is reluctant to turn on the subtitles. 
Class is one thing, homework is another thing, exam and class, homework is rarely related
Moved through slides very quickly, gave very challenging midterms (average 55%, median 52%), blamed the students for not practicing enough.

She is happy to explain concepts during office hours. Her marking scheme is generous and tries to give you the highest grade possible. During lectures she tends to over-explain simple topics and rush through more complex ones. The online lab for this course sucks but that's not her fault
She is just so Amazing. She cares so much and her passion for orgo makes the class very enjoyable. So much respect for her!

Dr. El Nachef is a decent teacher. She cares about the success of her students, so much so as she regraded an entire midterm to try and boost grades. She does go a little slow in the lecture, but this can also be helpful. Tests are essentially the same as the practice ones given. Very helpful when asked questions.

Dr. El Nachef fournit des diapos très organisés, et des exercices de pratique. Tout est là pour bien réussir, il faut juste mettre l'effort et étudier fort, parce que c'est pas un cours facile. The bad rating you see is because the course is hard, not because she's a bad prof.

One of my favorite chemistry professors so far. She really does make orgo 2 much more digestible and its clear she works hard to ensure all her student get the best grade possible. Her tests are very fair, as long as you go to lectures and complete the practice sets. Going to DGD's are also very helpful.
Good at explaining, hard midterms.

Decent prof all things considered. She does have a slight accent but nothing off putting. I did well but that being said this is ORGO 2. Study all the content. Do all the practice problems and attend all DGDs. Do all that and you should do well.

El Nachef is a solid choice for an orgo prof. People hate on the prof for the subject itself but if you study, do all the practice problems and do her past exams, there should be no reason you don't do well in her class.
Professor El Nachef is overall is good prof. Organic chemistry is a hard class. Study, do all the exercises she posts and you should be fine. The final was harder (cumulative).
Kind and gentle, but examples in the lecture do not represent the level of difficulty seen in the midterms. Rushed towards the end due to lack of time. DGD's are helpful, but that's about it.

She's very kind and devoted. Organic chemistry is just a hard class in general. It was rushed towards the end which made it hard to grasp concepts. The exams were also very difficult. To do well you really have to do lots of practice exercices and attend office hours.

She's a nice lady ill give her that but that's where the positivity stops. She's an awful prof, her explanation makes 0 sense, her powerpoints are illegible and she goes on and on about concepts that are not seen on the exams. Overall a class that's will guarantee to lower your grade and will increase your breakdowns per week. Goodluck.

Looking at a lot of these reviews, I was honestly super surprised as I thought El-Nachef was going to be an excellent teacher, unfortunately, my expectations were not met in the slightest. I tried following her explanations all semester and was left more confused than before I entered the class. She gave harder exams than other chem profs. AWFUL.
It was so hard to follow along with anything she was saying and don't get me started with her tests. Honestly, profs like her are the reason rate my prof should have negative rating options.
by far the worst prof i've ever had. she's terrible at explaining key concepts, her tests are unnecessarily hard and lectures are boring. avoid at all costs
Talks too much. Unclear. Makes orgo 100 times harder than it supposed to be. If you want a class that will single handily ruin your GPA orgo with El-Nachef is your way to go
Horrible horrible horrible class. Exams are written up as if she wants to trick you and she wants you to fail, funny when she can't even teach BASIC concepts properly.

The worst chem prof I have ever had in my entire life, legit sucked my passion for the subject out of me. Her explanations make no sense and you are left figuring out everything on your own. Orgo is hard on its own but El-Nachef makes it incomprehensible. Avoid at all cost!!!
AVOID THIS TEACHER

None of the examples seen in class were reflected on the exams. Her exams are so much harder than the practice exams handed out. It legit looks like she wants her students to fail. Talks way too much in the lecture, leaving students more confused and rushes through very important concepts. NO PRACTICE FINAL EXAM EITHER!! Run while u still can.

Prof El Nachef is a good prof, organic chemistry is hard. Overall, she explains things well, but tends to rush at the end because we're missing some time. We appreciate the 10% TopHat component that can save lol. Study hard and you'll pass. Also, go to class if you want to pass.

Nachef isn't good at teaching, she over complicates the concepts and doesn't do enough exemples in class (too much theory; not on exam). exams are horrible and hard. none of the examples done in class were similar to the exam. labs for this class are long and require a lot of work. it's definitely the class i put most effort in and barely passed
Worst prof I have ever had. Makes 0 sense, and leaves you more confused than before. Youtube is legit your best friend in this course. Good luck
If I could sum it up in word; Horrible.

Worst prof ever talks way too much, can't teach if her life depended on it and her exams are way harder than anything seen in class. If you have the chance, do yourself the favor and avoid this class at all costs.

Pros: very kind, organized, graders are VERY lenient/give extra points just because (probably from pity) Cons: tests are much harder than practice test, sooo much work especially for labs (not her fault really) I spent more time on this class than my 4 others combined, tests are long and content heavy, expectations arent very clear

Prof. Nachef is considered as a good chem's prof like she organizes the lectures perfectly and inspirationally teaches. However, her tests and finals are kinda condense and heavy. If you well-prepare the contents, you'd ensure to pass the class with an A. GOOD LUCK Y'ALL

Organic chemistry is a hard class, that's a given. I found her a great lecturer but sometimes she goes over the concept and practice problems in class really fast. The assignments were easy and the problem sets were a great practice for the midterms and final. Be on top of your game: study regularly and don't put everything at the last minute!

I didn't find her to be an amazing prof. She spends a lot of time explaining topics verbally without much written notes and it gets kind of confusing at times. Problems she goes over in class are VERY basic compared to the tests so best to practice A LOT. Her tests are similar in difficulty to the practice sets she posts.

El Machef is a very fair prof. If you do your work diligently, attend group discussions and do the problem sets she uploads, you will be fine. Her course very well organized and you know what to expect. If you just understand her slides and practice mechanisms at your own time, that A is yours my friend.

Organic chemistry is a hard subject, but Professor El Nachef makes it bearable. She does lecture rather quickly, but she explains concepts clearly and gives us the resources to do well (practice sets, past midterms, etc). Shes a pretty fair marker, so the effort you put into class is directly reflected in your grade. All in all, a solid choice.

Online class*. I had taken Orgo 1 more than a year ago and did not remember much from it. When she takes the time to explain a concept, I fully understood it. She does go fast but if you ask her to go back she will. Her exams grading criteria were not clear because it was online. This class requires ALOT of work if you want to pass. Work hard.

I took this class during an online semester. I passed the prerequisite (orgo 1) with misunderstandings but Claudia helped getting rid of all of them. Her exams are hard but still very fair. There are no surprises. She is an AMAZING professor and explains so well I would love to have her again even though her exams are a bit hard u gotta study!
Super!

This professor isnt clear with her explanations, she speaks way too quickly, has an accent that I found hard to understand and often slips in bits of French when lecturing (I was in the English section) which ads to the confusion. She also goes back and says yes/no, corrects her errors, and is late with uploading notes and replying to emails.

Since the moment I stepped foot into this class I knew I was gonna fail. Did I? No but still she sucks. Dont even bother going to class because her explanations sucks and she's expects you to already know everything. Her tests are straight forward but you had to teach yourself everything. Her slides only TEACHES theory but her tests are application

Honestly, Organic chemistry 2 with Dr. El Nachef was amazing. Her lectures are really informative and you learn a lot by going to her classes. Prior to this class, I never went to DGDs, but her's proved to be very useful. Learned much more in her review class of Orgo 1, than I did in all of Orgo 1.

She's a great prof. Would take it again anytime. Super caring, she wants everyone to pass. Also, she's accessible outside of class. Because it's orgo chem, it's a hard class but she makes it easier to understand.

I really liked her. We were going pretty slowly through the slides because she was taking her time to explain things, which I really liked but I was scared that towards the end she would have to go really fast but now we won't know because of Covid-19... But she answers all the questions and makes sure everyone understands

Claudia est tellement gentille ! Elle explique très bien la matière et n'arrête pas d'expliquer un concept avant que la grande majorité de la classe comprend. Ses examens sont tous des problèmes vus en classe et qu'on a pratiqué dans les exercises sur Brightspace. En général, excellente prof !

Amazing prof! Very caring and wants you to succeed :) Tries her best to make sure you understand the concepts. Both midterms and the final are fair, make sure to do the problem sets!!! I loved this class!

prof Claudia is the best organic prof I have ever had in my life. She is an amazing prof, caring, and she can inspire you if you like organic chemistry. The course is very heavy and its hard to keep catching up, so better to practice every day and do not wait until the last day!otherwise it is almost impossible to get a good grade.

Claudia is great at teaching in class. I had her for organic chem 2 and my only complaint is that she went over carbonyls very quick since she ran out of time. However, the midterms were fair and similar to previous midterms. As for the final, do the problem set and make sure you understand it and you'll do fine .

She explains the concepts really well in her lectures and even takes questions in the middle of them. She obviously cares about students doing well in her class and is helpful during office hours, but her midterms were near impossible to prepare for.

Claudia is hands down the most amazing orgo prof! She's such a caring and sweet lady who only wants the best for her students. Her lectures were phenomenal, I myself didn't excel in organic chemistry 2 but it was still my most favourite class because of Claudia. She's very clear, explains the material well and really just makes you enjoy orgo!
She's an awesome prof, but the course itself is hard. If you listen during the lectures and keep up with studying consistently, you should be ok

She does not spend enough time explaining the most important things are on the exams (making the lectures next to useless). The problem sets she provides does not properly prepare you for the exams. Although she wants students to do well, her exams are very difficult compared to what is shown in class and the questions in her problem sets. Avoid!
SUPER! J'ai adoré. Très bonne comme prof

I have taken Orgo 2 twice with her. First time, it was her first time teaching (because of that she did not know the threshold). Second time, she actually had improved and was more flexible in term of the material in explaining the material. Just do her practice problems on focus on doing all of them. Her exams were similar/ the same.
Great prof. Clear and thorough explanation and very helpful outside of class.

She's not clear during lecture, so unless you read the lecture in the 3 hours before class that she posted the material, get ready for confusion and a whole lot of participation lol. Other than that, she's a down-to-earth prof who cares about her students. Her assignments are like Ogilvie's - (protip) do them AGAIN AND AGAIN!

One of the best professors in the university. Everyone keeps complaining her exams are hard but they are not. They are very fair and reasonable. Organic is all about practice and if you dont thats when you get a bad grade. Her questions are very similar to the practice problem sets. Same concept just different molecules. Def take her again.

She is very kind and caring but rushes through materially and barely touches on important topics. Has extremely challenging exams, which are difficult to prepare for even if you complete all practice questions given. You will think that you understand a topic and then the exam will completely screw you over. Talks very quickly.

Claudia is a great professor and she is also super nice. Her slides are really good and she does a good job explaining the different concept. Her midterms were easy, however the final is pretty hard but definitely manageable. Just make sure to do all the practice problems and you'll do fine.
Best organic chemistry prof - she doesn't do that stupid flipped class

Very approachable and cares about making us understand the topics. She specializes in organic chemistry and still managed to deliver good lectures. Very honest and admits to sometimes not knowing the answer to questions outside of her comfort zone and would follow up with answers. Wish my other profs care as much as she does!
Really good for her first time teaching this class, would recommend

Slides are limited, and information was a combination of multiple textbook together. I couldn't find the pictures she used from the textbook. No very specific with what's on the midterm and exam. She saids everything was "feasible" but really it wasn't. If only she could have taught better.

El Nachef WANTS students to do well, but her execution in doing so is very poor. I used the textbook A LOT in this class (use slides as a study guide, but I recommend using the textbook for actual learning) and it was extremely helpful as the concepts she teaches are usually not clear. Go to class for attendance marks and beware of the final.

This class was a roller coaster ride and a genuinely mind boggling experience. I came into it expecting to die and got slapped in the face with a raw chicken breast coming out of every midterm. Then we would get our marks back and the lord himself would smile upon me somehow and pull me through. My advice is study hard and hope for the best.

Lectures were heavy, could not access to the online lectures because they were all blank on screen. Lecture slices covered only little things. Course was hard but the professor was not doing her best to simplify the problems. Hard midterms and finals.

It's a shame how out of 300+ students in the class few disgruntled students can ruine a professor's reputation on a public site such as this. I took this class. It was difficult at times but not impossible as some make it sound. Claudia is a good young professor and I'll be more than happy to have her as my prof again.

Imo she's not THAT bad. She's not great at lecturing but is very nice and tries her best to explain concepts in office hours. Her midterms are FAIR and final's fairly easy if you practiced problem sets. Orgo is a tough course in general so you have to wonder if everything is really the prof's fault or not. Overall glad I took her instead of Flynn
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Looking back, the midterms were difficult but FAIR. You have to work VERY HARD in this class if you want to do well. All necessary info provided in lecture. Marking was fair w/ bonus question and boost on overall grade. In Orgo 2 things are not clear cut like Orgo 1, BUT THAT'S JUST THE WAY CHEMICALS REACT so must THINK LIKE A MOLECULE (PRACTICE)!
Class attendance won't help you here. Claudia is the worst, don't take this course with her. Its scattered and unfair.

Throughout the semester Ive put so much time and effort into the course. Self teaching my self everything cause she couldnt teach. She literally tells you that you dont have to know certain things and they appear on the midterm and exams. As a 10 point GPA student I couldnt even handle her class. Just dont take her. Just bad.

As said before, orgo II is generally a hard course. There are a lot of concepts to learn/memorize/understand, and for people that rely on the prof to teach them everything they won't do well with Nachef. But if you put in the time to self-study, her midterms and especially exams were all fairly doable.

Worked my butt off for this course and passed with a 51.19%. This was the hardest course Ive ever taken and Dr. Nachef didnt do much to help. Lectures were not useful and I had to teach myself most of the material. While the midterms were fair the final was extremely difficult. DGDs were very helpful for this course however!

Know that Orgo II itself is a difficult course. She expects you to have a solid chem foundation for each lecture. And they are intense. She uses vocab like pKa and electrophile casually all the time, so stay focused on her lectures. But she gives part marks generously. Know her past midterms and slides. I wish she did more to reinforce our learning

Don't listen to the people on here. Claudia expects you to do work yourself, if you don't, you won't do well, but if you do (eg: doing the problem sets early, going to office hours for help), you'll do very well. Her midterms and final are super fair. She's a good prof, people just like to scapegoat, you can't slack in Orgo and just blame the prof.

The midterms were fairly difficult and had some tricky questions, but they were fair and she was very kind in office hours. She easily gave marks back where TAs were being bonobos. Her teaching wasn't the greatest, but let's be honest, that's the same for all the profs here. Final was easy with an easy 6% bonus. 1% bonus to final mark too!

Seems like a nice person but let me tell you I had absolutely no idea what was going on ever during class, get ready to teach yourself the entire course. Probably one of the hardest courses Ive taken yet

Worst prof ever. that's all I'm going to say. Asked her a question for confirmation on the exam and all she said was "Just read the question, It should be clear enough". I asked a questions because what she was asking for was unclear. Very disappointed. This is also how she is after class. What is clear to her isn't clear to students. Bad Prof.

She's very knowledgeable. There's no doubt about it. But SHE CAN NOT TEACH!! Has she ever heard of the concept of explicit teaching? She starts throwing in complicated concepts without explaining them because they are easy for her, but obviously we have no idea what she's talking about. Copy pasting from the textbook is not teaching.

The final exam is in less than 12 hours... I still don't understand anything despite attending class everyday and taking decent notes. She is boring to listen to, her power points are vague, she's not that great at explaining concepts. Her expectations for the class aren't very clear so its hard to study for her tests too. Please aVOID!

This prof has potential but she tends to rush through very important topics and does not clearly explain the material which makes it hard to know what to expect on midterms. She is not easy to contact outside of class and does not respond to emails. I would try to take this class with a different prof instead.

It seems like she's teaching in class, but ngl, for some reason I cannot understand what she is trying to say (and it's not cause of her accent either). For some reason the way she explains things just doesn't make sense (at least for me). s/o to Khan academy for coming clutch tho

Pretty hard course. Her lectures are essentially her presenting screenshots from the textbook and expectations aren't clear for the midterms, that are worth alot; she also has minimal weighting and no ways to get non-exam credit such as Sapling (besides 5% attendance)

A good prof, explains things well but her voice is a bit monotonous so it gets hard to concentrate sometimes. Takes attendance via TopHat so you can't skip class, and no homework so the grade is based on 2 midterms, attendance and a final. Pretty tough course material so only take it if it's mandatory for your program.
great professor
You win some you lose some. Her class is not a walk in the park but she's fair and she genuinely cares about making sure we understand the topics. Don't expect to pass without styding.
Terrible at teaching. Hard to follow along and her voice is annoying. Would not recommend, especially for Orgo 2.
great prof

Really nice prof, very approachable during office hours. Tests and quizzes were not too difficult if you studied. Class was somewhat rushed near the end due to lack of time. Extra credit was given. Class was somewhat rushed due to lack of time.

It was her first time teaching, and she did a very good job. Lectures were a bit quick, but she made up for it by being very useful in office hours. Exams were fair, though not easy, and she even gave the option for extra credit. Recommended.
Dr. Nachef is really great. She genuinely cares about you and is readily available if you have questions about course material. Her tests and exams are extremely fair, but it's definitely not easy.
